7. Expenditure arrears. The discovery of expenditure arrears from 2008 made fiscal management in 2009 more challenging. A stock take was conducted across spending units by external auditors through September 2009. Based on this exercise, the stock of domestic expenditure arrears at end-2008 was calculated at $\mathrm{GH}
ot\propto1.1$ billion (Table below). In 2009, arrears to domestic suppliers of goods and services were settled amounting to $\mathrm{GH}
ot\propto0.6$ billion. At the same time, reflecting revenue shortfalls and expenditure pressures, new payments arrears amounting to $\mathrm{GH}
ot\propto0.9$ billion (4.2 percent of GDP) were accumulated in 2009, of which more than half represented arrears to governmental statutory funds. This increased the stock of arrears at end-2009 to $\mathrm{GH}\phi1.4$ billion.

